<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n14217a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14217a">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14217a"> 217(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ari / mac Mar / Florida / Irland er Mikla / Gt. Ireland / Hvitra Manna / Land</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The connexion between Dublin and Iceland thus cemented by family ties continued throughout the ninth, tenth, and eleventh centuries, and the voyages for friendly intercourse, or commercial objects, led to the discovery of America by Norsemen connected with Dublin centuries before it was seen by Columbus. About the year 983 <mark>Ari, the son of Mar</mark>, a descendent of the Irish king Cearbhall, was wrecked on the coast of <mark>Florida, which he called &ldquo;Irland er Mikla,&rdquo; or Great Ireland</mark>, it being also termed &ldquo;<mark>Hvitra Manna Land</mark>,&rdquo; or Whitemens Land. <small> Charles Haliday, <a name="SKD1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SKD1"><cite title="source">The Scandinavian Kingdom of Dublin</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (1884) 105</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
